tty\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\"}, {\"begin\": 857, \"end\": 860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"score\": 0.9999094915019714, \"rank\": 9.042821967309285e-05, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my glasses\", \"from\": 797, \"to\": 807}, {\"ngram\": \"a reason\", \"from\": 815, \"to\": 823}, {\"ngram\": \"an emotional Pidcock\", \"from\": 826, \"to\": 846}, {\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 875, \"to\": 883}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 896}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Olympics is so special.\", \"from\": 898, \"to\": 926, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics\", \"from\": 899, \"to\": 911}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You never give up, you give everything, and that's what I had to do.\\\"\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 996, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 955, \"to\": 965}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock suffered anearly front puncture, and slightly botched wheel change,that looked set to end his chances.\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1108, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Pidcock\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1005}, {\"ngram\": \"front puncture\", \"from\": 1023, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"slightly botched wheel change\", \"from\": 1043, \"to\": 1072}, {\"ngram\": \"his chances\", \"from\": 1096, \"to\": 1107}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Thinks were going so well my mechanic was not ready,\\\" Pidcock said.\", \"from\": 1108, \"to\": 1176, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Thinks\", \"from\": 1109, \"to\": 1115}, {\"ngram\": \"my mechanic\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1146}, {\"ngram\": \"Pidcock\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1170}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But he did a super fast change in the end, my bike was perfect apart from the puncture.\\\"\", \"from\": 1177, \"to\": 1266, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a super fast change\", \"from\": 1189, \"to\": 1208}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 1212, \"to\": 1219}, {\"ngram\": \"my bike\", \"from\": 1221, \"to\": 1228}, {\"ngram\": \"the puncture\", \"from\": 1252, \"to\": 1264}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He put in a super human effort to regain the lead, before attacking almost immediately in an effort to drop Koretzky and South African Alan Hatherley.\", \"from\": 1268, \"to\": 1418, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a super human effort\", \"from\": 1278, \"to\": 1298}, {\"ngram\": \"the lead\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1317}, {\"ngram\": \"an effort\", \"from\": 1358, \"to\": 1367}, {\"ngram\": \"Koretzky and South African Alan Hatherley\", \"from\": 1376, \"to\": 1417}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Koretzky stuck to his wheel like glue, and launched his own savage attack at the top of the final climb, to open up a 20m gap on the Brit.\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1562, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Koretzky\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1432}, {\"ngram\": \"his wheel\", \"from\": 1442, \"to\": 1451}, {\"ngram\": \"glue\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1461}, {\"ngram\": \"his own savage attack\", \"from\": 1476, \"to\": 1497}, {\"ngram\": \"the top\", \"from\": 1501, \"to\": 1508}, {\"ngram\": \"the final climb\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1527}, {\"ngram\": \"a 20m gap\", \"from\": 1540, \"to\": 1549}, {\"ngram\": \"the Brit\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1561}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A bobble off camera brought the two riders back together on the final run-in to the finish, and Pidcock, seeing a split line around a tree, dived to the inside and accelerated, getting his wheel ahead of Koretzky before the tracks converged, and forcing the French rider to brake and unclip.\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1854, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1821, \"end\": 1827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.6792484407059587, \"rank\": 0.3875422049889685, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A bobble off camera\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1582}, {\"ngram\": \"the two riders\", \"from\": 1591, \"to\": 1605}, {\"ngram\": \"the final run-in\", \"from\": 1623, \"to\": 1639}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1653}, {\"ngram\": \"Pidcock\", \"from\": 1659, \"to\": 1666}, {\"ngram\": \"a split line\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1687}, {\"ngram\": \"a tree\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1701}, {\"ngram\": \"the inside\", \"from\": 1712, \"to\": 1722}, {\"ngram\": \"his wheel\", \"from\": 1748, \"to\": 1757}, {\"ngram\": \"Koretzky\", \"from\": 1767, \"to\": 1775}, {\"ngram\": \"the tracks\", \"from\": 1783, \"to\": 1793}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This was enough to create a gap and earn Pidcock his second Olympic XCO Gold medal.\", \"from\": 1855, \"to\": 1938, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a gap\", \"from\": 1881, \"to\": 1886}, {\"ngram\": \"Pidcock\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 1903}, {\"ngram\": \"his second Olympic XCO Gold medal\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 1937}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a post-race interview to Adam Blythe of Discovery Plus/Eurosport, Tom Pidcock was unapologetic about his last lap move; \\\"Rubbing's racing!\\\"\", \"from\": 1940, \"to\": 2082, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1968, \"end\": 1979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Blythe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Blythe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Blythe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Blythe\"}, {\"begin\": 2009, \"end\": 2020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"sco